# 🚀 TopUpPay — Production Deployment Guide

> **Stack:** Next.js 16 + Express 4 + PostgreSQL 17 + Nginx + Docker

---

## Architecture Overview

```
                     ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
Internet ──HTTPS──►  │          Nginx (port 443)           │
                     │  - SSL termination (Let's Encrypt)  │
                     │  - Gzip compression                 │
                     │  - Rate limiting                    │
                     │  - Security headers (HSTS, CSP)     │
                     └────────────┬──────────┬────────────┘
                                  │          │
                           /api/* │          │ /*
                                  ▼          ▼
                     ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐
                     │   Backend    │  │   Frontend   │
                     │  Express:4000│  │  Next.js:3000│
                     └──────┬───────┘  └──────────────┘
                            │
                            ▼
                     ┌──────────────┐
                     │  PostgreSQL  │
                     │  (internal)  │
                     └──────────────┘
```

---

## 1. Server Requirements

| Resource | Minimum | Recommended |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| CPU      | 1 vCPU  | 2 vCPU      |
| RAM      | 2 GB    | 4 GB        |
| Storage  | 20 GB   | 40 GB SSD   |
| OS       | Ubuntu 22.04 LTS | Ubuntu 22.04 LTS |

**Providers:** DigitalOcean Droplet, AWS EC2 t3.small, Vultr, Hetzner

---

## 2. Server Initial Setup

```bash
# Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install Docker
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sh
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
newgrp docker

# Install Docker Compose
sudo apt install docker-compose-plugin -y

# Install Certbot (for SSL)
sudo apt install certbot -y
```

---

## 3. Clone & Configure

```bash
# Clone your repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/top-up.git
cd top-up

# Copy env template and fill in real values
cp env.production.example .env.production
nano .env.production
```

### Required values in [.env.production](file:///Users/thoeurnratha/Documents/web-development/top-up/frontend/.env.production)

| Variable | Where to get |
|----------|-------------|
| `DB_PASSWORD` | Generate: `openssl rand -base64 32` |
| `BAKONG_ACCOUNT_ID` | [NBC Bakong portal](https://bakong.nbc.org.kh/) |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | `https://YOUR_DOMAIN.com/api` |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | `https://YOUR_DOMAIN.com` |
| `TOPUP_PROVIDER_*` | Your reseller agreement |

---

## 4. SSL Certificate

```bash
# Point your domain DNS A record to the server IP first!

# Get Let's Encrypt certificate
sudo certbot certonly --standalone \
  -d YOUR_DOMAIN.com \
  -d www.YOUR_DOMAIN.com \
  --email YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com \
  --agree-tos

# Copy certs to nginx/ssl/
sudo mkdir -p nginx/ssl
sudo cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/YOUR_DOMAIN.com/fullchain.pem nginx/ssl/
sudo cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/YOUR_DOMAIN.com/privkey.pem nginx/ssl/
sudo chmod 644 nginx/ssl/*.pem
```

---

## 5. Edit Nginx Config

Replace `YOUR_DOMAIN.com` in [nginx/nginx.conf](file:///Users/thoeurnratha/Documents/web-development/top-up/nginx/nginx.conf):

```bash
sed -i 's/YOUR_DOMAIN.com/topuppay.com/g' nginx/nginx.conf
```

---

## 6. Deploy

```bash
# Build and start all services
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml --env-file .env.production up -d --build

# Check all containers are healthy
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml ps

# View logs
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml logs -f
```

### Expected output
```
NAME         STATUS
db           healthy
backend      healthy
frontend     healthy
nginx        running
```

---

## 7. Seed the Database (First Deploy Only)

```bash
# Run seed script inside backend container
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml exec backend \
  node -e "
const { PrismaClient } = require('@prisma/client');
const p = new PrismaClient();
// Add your seed logic here
"
```

Or use Prisma Studio:
```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml exec backend npx prisma studio
```

---

## 8. Auto-Renew SSL

```bash
# Add to crontab (auto-renew every 60 days)
sudo crontab -e
# Add this line:
0 0 1 * * certbot renew --quiet && cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/YOUR_DOMAIN.com/*.pem /path/to/top-up/nginx/ssl/ && docker compose -f /path/to/top-up/docker-compose.prod.yml restart nginx
```

---

## 9. Updates & Redeployment

```bash
# Pull latest code
git pull origin main

# Rebuild and redeploy (zero-downtime with health checks)
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml --env-file .env.production up -d --build

# Database migrations are automatically applied on container start (entrypoint.sh)
```

---

## 10. Monitoring

```bash
# Check health endpoint
curl https://YOUR_DOMAIN.com/health

# Watch logs in real-time
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml logs -f backend

# Container resource usage
docker stats
```

---

## Security Checklist

- [x] Helmet security headers on backend
- [x] Rate limiting (20 req/15min on transactions)
- [x] CORS locked to production domain only
- [x] Non-root Docker user
- [x] HTTPS enforced (HTTP redirects to HTTPS)
- [x] HSTS header (max-age=31536000)
- [x] X-Frame-Options: DENY
- [x] No X-Powered-By header
- [x] PostgreSQL not exposed externally (internal network only)
- [x] Secrets in [.env.production](file:///Users/thoeurnratha/Documents/web-development/top-up/frontend/.env.production) (never in git)
- [x] Input size limit (10KB max body)
- [ ] Set up Sentry for error tracking (optional)
- [ ] Set up UptimeRobot/Better Uptime for monitoring (optional)

